Include this file in kernel or user space programs immediatetly after including @header{sys/npi.h}.

This header file is normally installed in the @file{/usr/include/strsctp} directory, so remember to
add @samp{-I/usr/include/strsctp} to your compile line.
@item sys/tpi_sctp.h
The @header{sys/npi_sctp.h} header file provides the Transport Provider Interface (TPI) definitions for
Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) that are common to the kernel and user space programs.
Include this file in kernel space programs immediately after including @header{sys/tihdr.h}, or user
space programs immediatetly after including @header{sys/tiuser.h}.

This header file is normally installed in the @file{/usr/include/strsctp} directory, so remember to
add @samp{-I/usr/include/strsctp} to your compile line.
